BY TIMOTHY AGBOR There was confusion at a hotel in Ikere-Ekiti, headquarters of Ikere Local Government Area of Ekiti State on Monday when a herbalist slumped in one of the hotel rooms and died few seconds after a sex romp with his female lover said to be a pastor’s wife. The middle-aged deceased, simply identified as Kehinde and said to be a popular native doctor in the community, had lodged in one of the hotel rooms with his female friend whose name could not be ascertained as at the time of filing this report. It was gathered that the woman, said to be a wife to a cleric in one of the churches in the community, had raised the alarm when Kehinde started behaving strangely after a round of sexual intercourse with her. A source in the area informed The Point that the woman might have been laced with thunderbolt, popularly known as ‘Magun’ in Yoruba parlance. Kehinde was said to have been confirmed dead after being rushed to a nearby hospital by the hotel manager and other staff When contacted, the Police Public Relations Officer in Ekiti state, ASP Sunday Abutu, confirmed the incident. Abutu said investigations had commenced on the circumstances leading to the death of the man, adding that the woman has been arrested by the police.